80
00:04:28,650 --> 00:04:29,550
Thank you for your help.

81
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:30,600
Thank you very much.
Thank you.

82
00:04:31,660 --> 00:04:32,300
Thank you.

83
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:33,950
We're entrusting this to you.
Thank you for your hard work.

84
00:04:35,850 --> 00:04:39,440
They promised to strengthen patrols during school hours.

85
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:42,220
Sorry for making you worry.

86
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:45,650
Teacher.

87
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:48,450
Teacher Ai.

88
00:04:50,060 --> 00:04:51,540
Can you please reconsider?

89
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,840
Huh? The contract we just signed?

90
00:04:54,260 --> 00:04:55,220
No

91
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:56,840
I'm talking about that man.

92
00:04:57,820 --> 00:04:59,970
Buying a man is utterly ridiculous.

93
00:05:00,410 --> 00:05:03,660
If this gets out online,
your popular writer career is ruined.

94
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:06,180
I don't do returns.

95
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:09,790
You seriously want to spend your future with him?

96
00:05:09,790 --> 00:05:10,690
Of course not!

97
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:12,570
But...

98
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:15,540
this is what I decided.

99
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:25,830
In that case, I've got an idea.

100
00:05:40,850 --> 00:05:41,640
Hmm?

101
00:05:45,730 --> 00:05:47,530
Today's test results are on the table.

102
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:56,520
Looks like it's okay even if we run out of condoms.

103
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:59,570
Shut up!

104
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,940
And what are you cooking,
acting like this is totally normal?

105
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:08,420
If you eat raw pork, all those tests would be wasted.

106
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:12,470
I told you not to cook

107
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:13,680
order takeout...!

108
00:06:14,490 --> 00:06:15,570
It's cheaper to cook it on our own.

109
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:21,060
Teacher Ai doesn't eat food like this.

110
00:06:21,460 --> 00:06:22,340
Why not?

111
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:23,660
Does he drink gasoline or something?

112
00:06:25,890 --> 00:06:27,500
Maybe.

113
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,190
What is he, a monster?

114
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,560
I have no idea what you're talking about.

115
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:32,550
Huh?

116
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:33,980
Ai-san is incredible.

117
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:35,420
He's someone who drinks gasoline.

118
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:37,550
Please don't say that with respect.

119
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:38,850
Yes.

120
00:06:43,450 --> 00:06:46,130
Please ask if anything is unclear.

121
00:06:46,530 --> 00:06:47,260
This is...

122
00:06:48,170 --> 00:06:50,040
A cohabitation agreement.

123
00:06:50,870 --> 00:06:54,080
If there's anything you disagree with or lacks,
please tell me.

124
00:06:57,690 --> 00:07:01,130
It mainly outlines the obligations for both of you.

125
00:07:02,210 --> 00:07:04,140
Teacher will pay for living expenses.

126
00:07:05,150 --> 00:07:07,800
And you can't do things the teacher dislikes.

127
00:07:09,330 --> 00:07:11,960
Party A reserves the right of termination.

128
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:16,070
Meaning if Ai-san gets tired of me,
he can just kick me out whenever?

129
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:17,470
Precisely.

130
00:07:18,260 --> 00:07:19,970
What if I refuse?

131
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:21,590
That's not an option.

132
00:07:21,810 --> 00:07:22,870
This is non-negotiable.

133
00:07:25,130 --> 00:07:26,820
Name your conditions.

134
00:07:27,630 --> 00:07:31,480
If you want to study, he'll send you.
He'll support anything you want to do.

135
00:07:32,110 --> 00:07:33,200
However...

136
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:35,060
non-negotiable terms must be followed.

137
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:37,660
Especially...

138
00:07:38,110 --> 00:07:39,730
the prohibition of romance.

139
00:07:40,910 --> 00:07:42,210
I agree.

140
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:44,360
Then let's continue.

141
00:07:45,780 --> 00:07:47,590
Payment will be made monthly.

142
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:51,650
Food, accommodation, and other necessary
expenses will be covered separately.

143
00:07:52,580 --> 00:07:54,370
Do writers make that much money?

144
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:56,580
Besides novels

145
00:07:56,990 --> 00:07:58,180
there are other income sources.

146
00:07:58,620 --> 00:07:59,390
And...

147
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:00,660
my family was rich originally.

148
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:02,530
So...

149
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,010
how much do you want?

150
00:08:04,930 --> 00:08:05,760
Whatever you decide

151
00:08:06,210 --> 00:08:07,130
I'll let Ai-san decide.

152
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,840
Then the agreement is done.

153
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:23,370
Is it good?

154
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:25,550
Delicious.

155
00:08:41,670 --> 00:08:43,950
Now officially a sugar daddy on paper.

156
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:45,660
So you approve.

157
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:48,300
I do not approve.

158
00:08:48,870 --> 00:08:50,470
This is a temporary arrangement.

159
00:08:50,990 --> 00:08:52,430
Ai-san is my sugar daddy?

160
00:08:52,890 --> 00:08:53,300
Hmm?
Isn't he?

161
00:08:57,490 --> 00:08:59,350
I'm the kitten's daddy.

162
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:01,520
Well, Ai has good taste.

163
00:09:01,820 --> 00:09:02,820
What's good about it?

164
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:03,810
Huh?

165
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:06,130
Upset that your beloved teacher was taken away?

166
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:10,750
- I didn't mean that.
- Well, it can't be helped.

167
00:09:10,790 --> 00:09:12,630
Women don't have "that thing".

168
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,110
Exactly.

169
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,870
Though I love Fumi

170
00:09:16,630 --> 00:09:17,710
since she doesn't have "that thing".

171
00:09:18,590 --> 00:09:19,770
I can't love her in that way.

172
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:22,930
You're both the same.

173
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:24,440
Birds of a feather.

174
00:09:24,690 --> 00:09:25,740
Thick as thieves.

175
00:09:27,180 --> 00:09:28,170
So, in other words...

176
00:09:28,380 --> 00:09:30,430
I have "that thing," you love me.

177
00:09:32,730 --> 00:09:33,700
How wonderful.

178
00:09:35,460 --> 00:09:37,610
It's easier to love someone than to abandon them.

179
00:09:38,490 --> 00:09:39,180
Well?

180
00:09:41,310 --> 00:09:42,240
So boring.

181
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:45,790
Just one thing...

182
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:47,700
I want to buy spare clothes.

183
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:48,900
Where's a good store?

184
00:09:49,930 --> 00:09:50,760
Fumi.

185
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,610
Go buy some for him tomorrow.

186
00:09:54,230 --> 00:09:55,270
Me?

187
00:09:55,770 --> 00:09:57,020
Food, clothing, and housing guarantee.

188
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,130
Isn't that in the contract?

189
00:09:58,830 --> 00:09:59,520
Or...
You want me to go?

190
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:01,950
Well then.

191
00:10:02,110 --> 00:10:03,770
Sorry, please get me some underwear, too.

192
00:10:03,970 --> 00:10:04,770
Underwear!
You heard.

193
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:06,450
Underwear.
Underwear!

194
00:10:07,950 --> 00:10:08,200
Why...

195
00:10:08,270 --> 00:10:09,280
is it me?

196
00:10:17,310 --> 00:10:19,710
Environmental protection is in your hands, go for it.

197
00:10:20,570 --> 00:10:22,190
Thanks for dropping me off.

198
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:27,620
I signed it.

199
00:10:28,270 --> 00:10:30,040
So now, I'm all yours, Ai-san.

200
00:10:30,640 --> 00:10:31,420
Also...

201
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:32,460
About the terms.

202
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:37,420
Anything else you want to add?

203
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:38,600
No.

204
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:40,930
About the prohibition of romance...

205
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:42,850
It means exactly what it says.

206
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,210
I have no interest in those romantic fantasies...

207
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,670
and think they're a waste of time.

208
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,780
Between us...

209
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,850
there will only be sex, that's the contract.

210
00:10:52,710 --> 00:10:54,300
You don't believe in love.

211
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:56,680
I'm so sick of hearing that.

212
00:11:00,090 --> 00:11:02,630
But some things can't be bound by written words.

213
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:06,220
You can't stop me from loving you.

214
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:11,260
I could never love you.

215
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,480
Kissing isn't prohibited.

216
00:11:22,490 --> 00:11:23,250
Right?

217
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:27,500
You are forbidden from doing anything I dislike.

218
00:11:28,470 --> 00:11:29,590
I like it.

219
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:31,890
Call me anytime

220
00:11:32,110 --> 00:11:33,670
I will be at your service.

221
00:11:40,110 --> 00:11:41,210
What just happened...

222
00:11:42,090 --> 00:11:43,030
Think it over.

223
00:11:50,820 --> 00:11:52,000
Don't command me.

224
00:12:04,110 --> 00:12:05,490
I will guide you.

225
00:12:06,580 --> 00:12:07,240
Understand..

226
00:12:21,770 --> 00:12:22,520
New book...

227
00:12:22,970 --> 00:12:23,700
Urban.

228
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:31,640
What is love...

229
00:12:39,580 --> 00:12:40,990
Love is too boring.

230
00:12:59,070 --> 00:13:00,460
You're too conspicuous.

231
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:01,740
Radiating star aura

232
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:03,310
I'm not hiding.

233
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:07,220
It's your day off, you don't have to be with me.

234
00:13:08,060 --> 00:13:10,340
Even on vacation I get photographed

235
00:13:10,650 --> 00:13:11,850
I don't really have holidays.

236
00:13:12,530 --> 00:13:14,180
Since I'll be photographed anyway...

237
00:13:15,890 --> 00:13:18,250
might as well use "Crazy for New Love" as the headline.

238
00:13:29,540 --> 00:13:30,490
Shirts and...

239
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:31,850
pants...

240
00:13:32,370 --> 00:13:33,720
buy ten sets each for replacement...

241
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:35,810
planning to wear them to the next life?

242
00:13:36,850 --> 00:13:37,680
Who knows...

243
00:13:39,310 --> 00:13:40,460
Teacher Ai...

244
00:13:40,590 --> 00:13:42,710
did he fall into that person's trap?

245
00:13:43,570 --> 00:13:45,020
I wouldn't call it a trap...

246
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:47,260
he might have fallen in love.

247
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:48,960
What?

248
00:13:49,260 --> 00:13:50,170
What's there to worry about?

249
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,490
I'm worried.

250
00:13:54,580 --> 00:13:56,430
Shouldn't you be more excited?

251
00:13:56,820 --> 00:13:58,130
Ai Rakumoto...

252
00:13:58,140 --> 00:14:00,650
maybe he can get rid of the destructive writing style.

253
00:14:01,180 --> 00:14:02,620
This might be his last chance.

254
00:14:07,190 --> 00:14:07,800
Let's go.

255
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:12,560
- Let's get something to eat first.
- Okay.

256
00:14:12,690 --> 00:14:13,490
What do you want?

257
00:14:20,740 --> 00:14:21,600
You're awake.

258
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:24,920
Don't barge in without permission

259
00:14:24,930 --> 00:14:27,050
I knocked, and I'm hungry.

260
00:14:27,210 --> 00:14:30,760
- You can order delivery.
- My phone's dead.

261
00:14:36,620 --> 00:14:37,770
Let's go out to eat.

262
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:42,000
- I have no appetite.
- The contract guarantees my food, clothing, housing.

263
00:14:42,620 --> 00:14:44,940
I'm really starving.

264
00:14:47,780 --> 00:14:49,020
You said it yourself, didn't you?

265
00:14:49,450 --> 00:14:51,300
That you'd do anything Kaishin asks.

266
00:14:53,230 --> 00:14:54,980
I want to eat with you, Ai-san.

267
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:57,250
Please.

268
00:15:11,230 --> 00:15:12,770
Quiet water...

269
00:15:14,070 --> 00:15:15,600
Spring water...

270
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:16,760
What can I get for you?

271
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:19,300
The assorted stew...

272
00:15:23,810 --> 00:15:28,930
I'll have clear broth mountain vegetables sweetfish,
fried bamboo fish balls, and miso grilled duck.

273
00:15:30,390 --> 00:15:31,180
How about you?

274
00:15:32,180 --> 00:15:33,420
You can just order for me, Ai-san.

275
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,450
Anything is fine.

276
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:37,060
Alright then...

277
00:15:37,510 --> 00:15:41,340
fresh tofu skin, fan-shaped turnip tempura,
Hida beef and spring water pork loin.

278
00:15:41,460 --> 00:15:43,040
And two cold-brewed green teas.

279
00:15:44,970 --> 00:15:46,770
Yes, right away.

280
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:50,590
We can share, if you like.

281
00:15:52,190 --> 00:15:53,320
Sounded like a spell.

282
00:15:54,330 --> 00:15:55,600
Sorry for embarrassing you.

283
00:15:56,740 --> 00:15:57,940
Who made you think that?

284
00:15:59,740 --> 00:16:00,700
Was it the waiter just now?

285
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:05,870
Where are you going?

286
00:16:06,570 --> 00:16:07,380
